  Grounding: Carpenter et al. (1998), Koger & Victor (2009),
  Hojnacki & Kimball (1998). Shared lobbyists and lobbying firms
  create information bridges; bill-level adoption ordering tests
  whether those bridges predict the direction of legislative adoption.

  Loaded 8,173 (edge, bill) records  and 3,712 RBO edge records.

